con:testCase.con:description:
Description : Member Login Input : Reads UserName form CreateMember2_Result table Output: Generates the 4 step authentication process that confirms that the member login has passed successfully
Results Database Name : Performance Table : MemberLogin_Result

con:config.con:query: SELECT * FROM CLASSROOM WHERE END_DT>SYSDATE AND STATUS='Approved' AND IS_COMPLETED=0 AND NICKNAME like 'RA%'

SELECT TO_CHAR(MIN(START_DT_TIME),'YYYY-MM-DD hh24:mi:ss'),TO_CHAR(MIN(END_DT_TIME),'YYYY-MM-DD hh24:mi:ss') FROM CALENDAR_EVENT WHERE START_DT_TIME>SYSDATE AND CLASSROOM_ID='${Property#classroomID}' ORDER BY PROGRAM_INTERVAL_NUMBER ASC

SELECT PROV.ID, PROV.EMAIL, CAST( START_DT_TIME AS TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE ) AT TIME ZONE 'AMERICA/NEW_YORK' START_DT_NY, CAST( END_DT_TIME AS TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE ) AT TIME ZONE 'AMERICA/NEW_YORK' END_DT_NY, HOST_ID, SESSION_STATUS, EVENT_TYPE , START_DT_TIME, END_DT_TIME FROM CALENDAR_EVENT EVT, PROVIDER PROV WHERE EVT.HOST_ID=PROV.ID AND PROV.IS_ACTIVE=1 AND EVT.HOST_ID IN (SELECT PROVIDER_ID FROM MP_PROVIDER_APPROVED WHERE SESSION_TYPE_ID IN ('01') AND WILL_DELIVER=1 AND IS_APPROVED=1) AND (
START_DT_TIME<=TO_DATE('${Property#startTime}','YYYY-MM-DD hh24:mi:ss') AND END_DT_TIME>TO_DATE('${Property#EndTime}','YYYY-MM-DD hh24:mi:ss') AND EVENT_TYPE='Available' )
